<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1849,2084]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis:—Pileus minute, white, attached dorsally to stems and the underside of leaves of living plants, basidiospores oblong, finely verrucose, cheilocystidia clavate, capitate, flexuous, occasionally apically branched, pileipellis a trichoderm, terminal cells occasionally slightly capitate.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1849,2084]" box="[189,1248,1953,1980]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">Etymology:—The epithet refers to the habitat of the species, namely, living herbaceous plants.</paragraph>
