<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,158,1373]" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,842,868]" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">Notes:</emphasis>
According to the classification proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Consiglio, G. &amp; Setti, L." box="[768,1067,842,868]" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" refId="ref4971" refString="Consiglio, G. &amp; Setti, L. (2008) Il genere Crepidotus in Europa. Associazione Micologica Bresadola, Trento, Italy, 344 pp." type="book" year="2008">Consiglio and Setti (2008)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="T. Bau &amp; Y. P. Ge" authorityYear="2022" box="[1079,1227,842,869]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="herbaceus">
<emphasis box="[1079,1227,842,869]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">C. herbaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be placed in series 
<taxonomicName authority="Consiglio &amp; Setti" authorityName="Consiglio &amp; Setti" box="[206,501,878,905]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="caspari">
<emphasis box="[206,296,879,905]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">Caspari</emphasis>
Consiglio &amp; Setti
</taxonomicName>
, section 
<emphasis box="[598,740,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">Dochmiopus</emphasis>
Consiglio &amp; Setti, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pat.) Pilat. On" authorityName="Pilat. On" baseAuthorityName="Pat." class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Dochmiopus">
<emphasis box="[954,1077,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">Crepidotus</emphasis>
subgen. 
<emphasis box="[1177,1319,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">Dochmiopus</emphasis>
(Pat.) Pilát. On
</taxonomicName>
basis of its minute pileus and smaller basidiospores, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="T. Bau &amp; Y. P. Ge" authorityYear="2022" box="[756,903,914,941]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="herbaceus">
<emphasis box="[756,903,914,941]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">C. herbaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from all five documented taxa of series 
<taxonomicName authority="(Consiglio &amp; Setti 2008)" baseAuthorityName="Consiglio &amp; Setti" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[207,588,950,977]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="caspari">
<emphasis box="[207,297,951,977]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">Caspari</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Consiglio, G. &amp; Setti, L." box="[313,580,950,976]" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" refId="ref4971" refString="Consiglio, G. &amp; Setti, L. (2008) Il genere Crepidotus in Europa. Associazione Micologica Bresadola, Trento, Italy, 344 pp." type="book" year="2008">Consiglio &amp; Setti 2008</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hesler, L. R. &amp; Smith, A. H." box="[599,857,950,977]" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" refId="ref7196" refString="Hesler, L. R. &amp; Smith, A. H. (1965) North American Species of Crepidotus. Hafner Publishing Company, New York, London, 168 pp." type="book" year="1965">Hesler &amp; Smith (1965)</bibRefCitation>
documented four species that produce basidiospores of similar size to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="T. Bau &amp; Y. P. Ge" authorityYear="2022" box="[328,476,986,1013]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="herbaceus">
<emphasis box="[328,476,986,1013]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">C. herbaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Hesler &amp; A. H. Smith (1965: 112)" authorityName="Hesler &amp; A. H. Smith" authorityPageNumber="112" authorityYear="1965" box="[490,1035,986,1013]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="ellipsoideus">
<emphasis box="[490,656,986,1013]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">C. ellipsoideus</emphasis>
Hesler &amp; A.H. Smith (1965: 112)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hesler &amp; A. H. Smith (1965: 113)" authorityName="Hesler &amp; A. H. Smith" authorityPageNumber="113" authorityYear="1965" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="lagenicystis">
<emphasis box="[1046,1211,986,1013]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">C. lagenicystis</emphasis>
Hesler &amp; A.H. Smith (1965: 113)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hesler &amp; A. H. Smith (1965: 92)" authorityName="Hesler &amp; A. H. Smith" authorityPageNumber="92" authorityYear="1965" box="[284,864,1022,1049]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="phaseoliformis">
<emphasis box="[284,484,1022,1049]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">C. phaseoliformis</emphasis>
Hesler &amp; A.H. Smith (1965: 92)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Hesler &amp; A. H. Smith (1965: 121)" authorityName="Hesler &amp; A. H. Smith" authorityPageNumber="121" authorityYear="1965" box="[927,1447,1022,1049]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="vulgaris">
<emphasis box="[927,1053,1022,1049]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">C. vulgaris</emphasis>
Hesler &amp; A.H. Smith (1965: 121)
</taxonomicName>
. Among these four species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hesler &amp; A. H. Smith" authorityYear="1965" box="[435,601,1058,1085]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="ellipsoideus">
<emphasis box="[435,601,1058,1085]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">C. ellipsoideus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hesler &amp; A. H. Smith" authorityYear="1965" box="[652,776,1058,1085]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="vulgaris">
<emphasis box="[652,776,1058,1085]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">C. vulgaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possess an apparently broader pileus, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hesler &amp; A. H. Smith" authorityYear="1965" box="[1245,1408,1058,1085]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="lagenicystis">
<emphasis box="[1245,1408,1058,1085]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">C. lagenicystis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has much larger, different-shaped cheilocystidia. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hesler &amp; A. H. Smith" authorityYear="1965" box="[634,928,1094,1120]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="phaseoliformis">
<emphasis box="[634,928,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">Crepidotus phaseoliformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a larger pileus and possesses filamentous to cylindric cheilocystidia. In addition, the basidiospores of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hesler &amp; A. H. Smith" authorityYear="1965" box="[772,970,1130,1157]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="phaseoliformis">
<emphasis box="[772,970,1130,1157]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">C. phaseoliformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are smooth, whereas those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="T. Bau &amp; Y. P. Ge" authorityYear="2022" box="[1305,1451,1130,1157]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="herbaceus">
<emphasis box="[1305,1451,1130,1157]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">C. herbaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are slightly punctate (under 1000× magnification) or indistinctly smooth (under 600× magnification).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="28" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,158,1373]" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. K. Pradeep &amp; A. M. Kumar" authorityYear="2018" box="[189,441,1202,1228]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="palodensis">
<emphasis box="[189,441,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">Crepidotus palodensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closest to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="T. Bau &amp; Y. P. Ge" authorityYear="2022" box="[588,737,1202,1229]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="herbaceus">
<emphasis box="[588,737,1202,1229]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">C. herbaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in pileus size and color, but 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. K. Pradeep &amp; A. M. Kumar" authorityYear="2018" box="[1064,1217,1202,1229]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="palodensis">
<emphasis box="[1064,1217,1202,1229]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">C. palodensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possess much larger basidiospores (8–10.5 × 4–5 μm) (
<bibRefCitation author="Kumar, A. M. &amp; Vrinda, K. B. &amp; Pradeep, C. K." box="[519,729,1238,1264]" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" pagination="67 - 78" refId="ref7847" refString="Kumar, A. M., Vrinda, K. B. &amp; Pradeep, C. K. (2018) Two new species of Crepidotus (Basidiomycota, Agaricales) from peninsular India. Phytotaxa 372: 67 - 78. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 372.1.5" type="journal article" year="2018">
Kumar 
<emphasis box="[605,661,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). In a BLASTn search using the nLSU sequence (
<accessionNumber box="[1281,1414,1238,1265]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/OM010350" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">OM010350</accessionNumber>
) of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="T. Bau &amp; Y. P. Ge" authorityYear="2022" box="[136,284,1274,1301]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="herbaceus">
<emphasis box="[136,284,1274,1301]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">C. herbaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a query, the closest hit was 
<taxonomicName authority="Peck (1886: 72)" authorityName="Peck" authorityPageNumber="72" authorityYear="1886" box="[634,949,1274,1301]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="versutus">
<emphasis box="[634,761,1275,1301]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">C. versutus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Peck, C. H." box="[769,949,1274,1300]" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" pagination="58 - 73" refId="ref8627" refString="Peck, C. H. (1886) New York species of Pleurotus, Claudopus and Crepidotus. Annual Report of the Trustees of the State Museum of Natural History 39: 58 - 73." type="journal article" year="1886">Peck (1886: 72)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<accessionNumber box="[964,1093,1274,1300]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/AY820890" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">AY820890</accessionNumber>
), with 97% sequence similarity, followed by 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Quelet" authorityYear="1888" baseAuthorityName="Fries" baseAuthorityYear="1821" box="[275,403,1310,1336]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="22" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="epibryus">
C. 
<emphasis box="[307,403,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">epibryus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<accessionNumber box="[417,552,1310,1337]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MK277886" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">MK277886</accessionNumber>
), with 97% sequence similarity. Our comparison of nLSU sequences in GenBank indicates that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="T. Bau &amp; Y. P. Ge" authorityYear="2022" box="[292,439,1346,1373]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Inocybaceae" genus="Crepidotus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="herbaceus">
<emphasis box="[292,439,1346,1373]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">C. herbaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a distinct taxon.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
